# EVMC4U local patches for RealtimeAvatarController (mocap-vmc spec)
#
# Pristine source : commit 464df2b (initial EVMC4U import, RealtimeAvatarController/Assets/EVMC4U/ExternalReceiver.cs)
# Target snapshot : commit e1d213e (HEAD at patch generation, 2026-04-23)
# Spec reference  : .kiro/specs/mocap-vmc/design.md §6 (EVMC4U local patches)
#
# This patch records the 4 local modifications applied to the vendored
# Assets/EVMC4U/ExternalReceiver.cs. The patches are also tagged in-source
# with `// [RealtimeAvatarController mocap-vmc local patch]` markers so
# they can be located when re-importing a newer EVMC4U release.
#
# Patch summary:
#   1. L1            : header marker comment pointing at design.md §6
#   2. L388-L422     : public read-only accessors for HumanBodyBones*Table /
#                      shutdown flag, Latest Root* cache properties, and
#                      InjectBone*ForTest setters (test/dev builds only)
#   3. L848-L850     : ProcessMessage Model=null early-return relaxation
#   4. L862-L918     : Root cache + Transform-write guard separation so the
#                      Adapter (Model=null path) keeps populating bone /
#                      root dictionaries while preserving the original
#                      Transform-write semantics when Model is supplied.
#
# How to apply (from repo root, on a pristine EVMC4U import):
#   git apply .kiro/specs/mocap-vmc/evmc4u.patch
#
# How to regenerate (after future patch edits):
#   git diff 464df2b..HEAD -- "RealtimeAvatarController/Assets/EVMC4U/ExternalReceiver.cs" > .kiro/specs/mocap-vmc/evmc4u.patch.body
#   (then re-attach this header)
#
diff --git a/RealtimeAvatarController/Assets/EVMC4U/ExternalReceiver.cs b/RealtimeAvatarController/Assets/EVMC4U/ExternalReceiver.cs
index a12dcf9..923580d 100644
